  "prompt": "What do Nobel Prize winners get?",
  "response": "Nobel Prize winners receive several things:\n\n1. A gold medal\n\u2022 Made of 18-karat gold\n\u2022 Depicts Alfred Nobel's image\n\u2022 Unique design for each prize category\n\n2. A cash award/monetary prize\n\u2022 Currently around $1 million (varies slightly each year)\n\u2022 Meant to support continued research or work\n\n3. A diploma/certificate\n\u2022 Officially recognizes the award\n\u2022 Beautifully designed and personalized\n\n4. International recognition\n\u2022 Prestigious global acknowledgment\n\u2022 Often leads to further opportunities in research or their field\n\n5. Ceremonial event\n\u2022 Formal award ceremony in Stockholm, Sweden (except Peace Prize, which is in Oslo, Norway)\n\u2022 Opportunity to give an acceptance speech\n\nThe prize is awarded in six categories: Physics, Chemistry, Physiology or Medicine, Literature, Peace, and Economic Sciences.\n\nThe monetary amount and specific details can vary slightly from year to year, but these are the core components of the Nobel Prize award.",
